{
    "publish_date": "2011-06-09T06:16:54.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT3M19S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "While I&#39;m working on some\nmore ambitious projects,", 
            "dur": "1.78", 
            "start": "0.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I wanted to quickly comment\non a couple of mathy things", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that have been floating\naround the internet, just", 
            "dur": "1.436", 
            "start": "4.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so you know I&#39;m still alive.", 
            "dur": "1.167", 
            "start": "5.646"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there&#39;s this video\nthat&#39;s been floating around", 
            "dur": "2.041", 
            "start": "6.813"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "about how to multiply\nvisually like this.", 
            "dur": "1.826", 
            "start": "8.854"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Pick two numbers,\nlet&#39;s say, 12 times 3.", 
            "dur": "2.751", 
            "start": "10.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then you draw these lines.", 
            "dur": "1.249", 
            "start": "13.431"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "12, 31.", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "14.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then you start counting\nthe intersections-- 1, 2,", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "17.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "3 on the left; 1, 2, 3,\n4, 5, 6, 7 in the middle;", 
            "dur": "2.91", 
            "start": "19.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "1, 2 on the right, put\nthem together, 3, 7, 2.", 
            "dur": "2.83", 
            "start": "22.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There&#39;s your answer.", 
            "dur": "0.88", 
            "start": "25.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Magic, right?", 
            "dur": "1.067", 
            "start": "26.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But one of the delightful\nthings about mathematics", 
            "dur": "2.083", 
            "start": "27.177"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is that there&#39;s often more than\none way to solve a problem.", 
            "dur": "2.18", 
            "start": "29.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And sometimes these methods\nlook entirely different,", 
            "dur": "2.166", 
            "start": "31.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but because they\ndo the same thing,", 
            "dur": "1.624", 
            "start": "33.606"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they must be connected somehow.", 
            "dur": "1.78", 
            "start": "35.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in this case, they&#39;re\nnot so different at all.", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "37.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let me demonstrate this\nvisual method again.", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "39.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This time, let&#39;s do 97 times 86.", 
            "dur": "2.88", 
            "start": "41.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we draw our nine\nlines and seven lines", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "44.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "time eight lines and six lines.", 
            "dur": "1.9", 
            "start": "47.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, all we have to do is count\nthe intersections-- 1,2, 3, 4,", 
            "dur": "2.847", 
            "start": "49.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10.", 
            "dur": "2.133", 
            "start": "52.057"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, wait.", 
            "dur": "0.68", 
            "start": "54.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is boring.", 
            "dur": "0.8", 
            "start": "54.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How about instead of\ncounting all the dots,", 
            "dur": "1.39", 
            "start": "55.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we just figure out how many\nintersections there are.", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "57.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s see, there&#39;s seven\ngoing one way and six", 
            "dur": "1.92", 
            "start": "59.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "going the other.", 
            "dur": "0.666", 
            "start": "61.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Hey, let&#39;s do 6 times\n7, which is-- huh.", 
            "dur": "2.824", 
            "start": "61.706"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Forget everything I\never said about learning", 
            "dur": "1.9", 
            "start": "64.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a certain amount of memorization\nin mathematics being useful,", 
            "dur": "2.91", 
            "start": "66.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at least at an\nelementary school level.", 
            "dur": "1.71", 
            "start": "69.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because apparently,\nI&#39;ve been faking my way", 
            "dur": "1.84", 
            "start": "71.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "through being a\nmathematician without having", 
            "dur": "1.833", 
            "start": "72.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "memorized 6 times 7.", 
            "dur": "1.897", 
            "start": "74.723"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And now I&#39;m going to have to\nfigure out 5 times 7, which", 
            "dur": "2.9", 
            "start": "76.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is half of 10 times 7,\nwhich is 70, so that&#39;s 35,", 
            "dur": "3.29", 
            "start": "79.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and then add the\nsixth 7 to get 42.", 
            "dur": "2.722", 
            "start": "82.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Wow, I really should\nhave known that one.", 
            "dur": "1.708", 
            "start": "85.532"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, but the point is that\nthis method breaks down", 
            "dur": "2.69", 
            "start": "87.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the two-digit\nmultiplication problem", 
            "dur": "1.74", 
            "start": "89.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into four one-digit\nmultiplication problems.", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "91.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if you do have your\nmultiplication table memorized,", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "94.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you can easily figure\nout the answers.", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "96.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And just like\nthese three numbers", 
            "dur": "1.43", 
            "start": "99.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "became the ones, tens, and\nhundreds place of the answer,", 
            "dur": "3.41", 
            "start": "100.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "these do, too-- ones,\ntens, hundreds-- and you", 
            "dur": "2.96", 
            "start": "104.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "add them up and voila!", 
            "dur": "1.6", 
            "start": "107.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which is exactly the same\nkind of breaking down", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "108.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into single-digit\nmultiplication and adding", 
            "dur": "1.81", 
            "start": "110.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that you do during\nthe old boring method.", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "112.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The whole point is just to\nmultiply every pair of digits,", 
            "dur": "2.46", 
            "start": "114.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "make sure you&#39;ve got the proper\nnumber of zeroes on the end,", 
            "dur": "2.499", 
            "start": "117.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and add them all up.", 
            "dur": "1.271", 
            "start": "119.569"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But of course, seeing that\nwhat you&#39;re actually doing", 
            "dur": "1.6", 
            "start": "120.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is multiplying\nevery possible pair", 
            "dur": "1.365", 
            "start": "122.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is not something your\nteachers want you to realize,", 
            "dur": "1.925", 
            "start": "123.805"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or else you might remember\nthe every combination concept", 
            "dur": "2.333", 
            "start": "125.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when you get to\nmultiplying binomials,", 
            "dur": "1.657", 
            "start": "128.063"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and it might make it too easy.", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "129.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the end, all of these\nmethods of multiplication", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "131.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "distract from what\nmultiplication really", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "133.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is, which for 12\ntimes 31 is this.", 
            "dur": "2.849", 
            "start": "135.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "All the rest is just\nbreaking it down", 
            "dur": "1.541", 
            "start": "138.349"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into well-organized chunks,\nsaying, well, 10 times 30", 
            "dur": "2.84", 
            "start": "139.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is this, 10 times 1 this, 30\ntimes 2 is that, and 2 times 1", 
            "dur": "3.58", 
            "start": "142.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is that.", 
            "dur": "0.76", 
            "start": "146.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Add them all up, and\nyou get the total area.", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "147.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Don&#39;t let notation get in the\nway of your understanding.", 
            "dur": "2.906", 
            "start": "149.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Speaking of notation, this\ninfuriating bit of nonsense", 
            "dur": "2.344", 
            "start": "152.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "has been circulating\naround recently.", 
            "dur": "2.127", 
            "start": "154.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that there has been so\nmuch discussion of it is sign", 
            "dur": "2.333", 
            "start": "156.867"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that we&#39;ve been trained to care\nabout notation way too much.", 
            "dur": "3.26", 
            "start": "159.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Do you multiply here first\nor divide here first?", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "162.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The answer is that this is\na badly formed sentence.", 
            "dur": "2.89", 
            "start": "164.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s like saying, I would like\nsome juice or water with ice.", 
            "dur": "3.272", 
            "start": "167.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Do you mean you&#39;d\nlike either juice", 
            "dur": "1.458", 
            "start": "170.922"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with no ice or water with ice?", 
            "dur": "1.51", 
            "start": "172.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or do you mean that you&#39;d like\neither juice with ice or water", 
            "dur": "2.87", 
            "start": "173.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with ice?", 
            "dur": "0.94", 
            "start": "176.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can make claims\nabout conventions", 
            "dur": "1.6", 
            "start": "177.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and what&#39;s right and wrong,\nbut really the burden", 
            "dur": "1.77", 
            "start": "179.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is on the author of the\nsentence to put in some commas", 
            "dur": "2.32", 
            "start": "181.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and make things clear.", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "183.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Mathematicians do this by\nadding parenthesis and avoiding", 
            "dur": "2.67", 
            "start": "184.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this divided by sign.", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "187.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Math is not marks on a page.", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "189.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The mathematics is in what\nthose marks represent.", 
            "dur": "2.75", 
            "start": "191.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can make up any rules\nyou want about stuff", 
            "dur": "2.285", 
            "start": "193.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as long as you&#39;re\nconsistent with them.", 
            "dur": "1.625", 
            "start": "196.245"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The end.", 
            "dur": "1.71", 
            "start": "197.87"
        }
    ], 
